Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of iterated-integral signatures and log signatures in machine learning and statistics, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithms presented in the paper for efficiently calculating these signatures could fall under the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of these signatures in characterizing the shape of a path could also relate to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper's focus on benchmarking the performance of the algorithms could suggest a connection to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the potential applications of these signatures in computer vision could relate to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
